SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMMUNITY OPTIONS HOPEWELL, INC. IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE US INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. ACCORDINGLY, NO PROVISION FOR FEDERAL INCOME TAX HAS BEEN RECORDED. THE ORGANIZATION ADOPTED THE ACCOUNTING PRONOUNCEMENT RELATED TO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2013. UPON ADOPTION OF THIS ACCOUNTING PRONOUNCEMENT, THE PROJECT HAD NO UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS. FURTHERMORE, THE PROJECT HAD NO UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS AT JUNE 30, 2018 AND 2017. THE PROJECT HAD NO INCOME TAX RELATED PENALTIES AND INTEREST FOR THE PERIOD ENDED JUNE 30, 2018.
OFFICERS OF COMMUNITY OPTIONS, INC RECEIVE BONUS COMPENSATION IN ADDITION TO SALARY IF OPERATIONAL OBJECTIVES ARE MET BY THE ORGANIZATION EACH FISCAL YEAR.

COMPENSATION IS DETERMINED BY PARENT ORGANIZATION, COMMUNITY OPTIONS, INC. COMMUNITY OPTIONS, INC. USES SEVERAL TOOLS TO ESTABLISH COMPENSATION INCLUDING INDEPENDENT COMPENSATION CONSULTANT AND COMPENSATION STUDIES. SALARY FOR ORGANIZATION'S CEO/EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR MUST BE APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: 990 DRAFT IS DISTRIBUTED TO EACH MEMBER OF THE GOVERNING BODY (THE FINANCE COMMITTEE)FOR REVIEW. SUBSEQUENTLY, MANAGEMENT OBTAINS APPROVAL CONFIRMATION FROM EACH MEMBER OF THE FINANCE COMMITTEE AND THEN THE FINAL 990 IS FILED. IN ADDITION THE FULL BOARD IS ALSO GIVEN A COPY OF THE 990 ONCE THE FINANCE COMMITTEE HAS REVIEWED AND APPROVED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ON AN ANNUAL BASIS, THE POLICY IS REVIEWED AND ALL BOARD MEMBERS ARE ASKED TO DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICTS. ALL CONFLICT FORMS FOR THE BOARD ARE REVIEWED AND DISCUSSED AND DOCUMENTED CONCLUSIONS ARE IN THE BOARD MINUTES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
